@jiaodong definitely agree with all the points you've made. Ideally, we can set the default value to be `SPREAD` and raise an exception if the user explicitly sets anything else.

However, since the current existing pattern is for all Trainers to share the same `ScalingConfig`, it's a pretty bad experience to have the user explicitly specify the `ScalingConfig` with `SPREAD` in order to use this Trainer.

My vote would be to just force convert to `SPREAD`, ignoring whatever value is passed in, until we have a better story around Trainer specific `ScalingConfig`s. Thoughts?

