Use of assert.Equal here ends up not validating the reference-based deletion because assert.Equal does a deep equals.

If you replace the assert.Equal LHS with `{pA, a, b1, b3, c}`, it will still pass because b2 deep equals b1.

To verify the new behavior correctly, we need to do a reference match.
testify does not include a referential matching helper
so the simplest way to verify this might be to loop through the slice and do `==` comparisons.

```go
// assert.Equals or assert.NotContains
// are not enough because b1 deep equals b2 and b3.
for _, s := range snap.Resources {
  assert.False(t, s == b1)
}
```

